               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">PETER SPENDER</hi>. I am a carpenter, and live in London-street. I had a plane, stock, bit, saw, and screw-driver, safe on the 26th of February—I left them on Saturday night, at seven o'clock, in a building where. I was it work at Kensington, and on Monday morning we found the building burst open, and the things gone—they are here—these four are mine, I will swear—we found this iron instrument on the work-bench, which would break the place open.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1133" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1133" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1133" type="surname" value="WOODWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1133" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>BENJAMIN WOODWARD</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 28th of February, the prisoner came to me, represented himself as a carpenter, and asked me to buy these tools—I said I did not care much about them—he said he was going to van Diemen's-land, emigrating, and gave me his address—I gave him 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did I not show them to you in a public-house? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, you came to me at my own door—it was day-light.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I met a poor man in distress, by the Docks; he said he was a carpenter, and had some tools to sell; he wanted 6<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for them, I gave him 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
